   "source": [
    "a = '1111'\n",
    "nq = len(a)+1\n",
    "\n",
    "bv = QuantumCircuit(nq, nq-1)\n",

    "bv.barrier()\n",
    "bv.cx(range(len(a)), nq-1)\n",
    "bv.barrier()\n",
    "bv.h(range(nq))\n",
    "bv.barrier()\n",
    "bv.measure(range(nq-1), range(nq-1))\n",
    "\n",

   "source": [
    "## Custom Noisy Simulation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "06ae053f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Build Readout Noise model using `ReadoutError` class"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "83a9a106",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Check [ReadoutError](https://qiskit.org/ecosystem/aer/stubs/qiskit_aer.noise.ReadoutError.html?highlight=readout+error#qiskit_aer.noise.ReadoutError)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c8e5ce59",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- Parameters \n",
    ": a list of assignment probability vectors $P(A|B)$ where $A$ and $B$ are noisy measurement outcomes and true measurement oucomes, respectively.  \n",
    "Explicitly, $P(A|B)= [P(A|k)]$ where $k\\in\\{0, 1, 2, ..., 2^n - 1\\}$ for $n$ number of qubits.\n",
    "\n",
    "    E.g. for 1 qubit case, $P(A|B) = [P(A|0), P(A|1)] = [[P(0|0), P(1|0)], [P(0|1), P(1|1)]]$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 77,
   "id": "9c1687e8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "ReadoutError on 1 qubits. Assignment probabilities:\n",
      " P(j|0) =  [0.9 0.1]\n",
      " P(j|1) =  [0.2 0.8]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "p10, p01 = 0.1, 0.2\n",
    "ro = ReadoutError([[1-p10, p10], [p01, 1-p01]])\n",
    "print(ro)\n",
    "\n",
    "ro_noise = NoiseModel()\n",
    "\n",
    "ro_noise.add_all_qubit_readout_error(ro)\n",
    "## alternative\n",
    "# ro_noise.add_readout_error(ro, [0])\n",
    "# ro_noise.add_readout_error(ro, [1])\n",
    "# ro_noise.add_readout_error(ro, [2])\n",
    "# ro_noise.add_readout_error(ro, [3])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 78,
   "id": "80f72063",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "NoiseModel:\n",
      "  Basis gates: ['cx', 'id', 'rz', 'sx']\n",
      "  Instructions with noise: ['measure']\n",
      "  All-qubits errors: ['measure']\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(ro_noise)"
   ]
  },

    "    <h3>Hands-on exercise 3.</h3>\n",
    "    <p>\n",
    "    Perform the noise simulation using two Samplers with resilience_level=0 (no error mitigation) and 1 (default, readout error mitigation) for the 5 qubit GHZ circuit in the cell below where the readout error for each qubit and coupling map are as follows.</p><br>\n",
    "      <p>\n",
    "         <li> Single qubit readout error for each qubit</li>   \n",
    "       $q0: P(0|0)=0.95, P(1|0)=0.05, P(0|1)=0.15, P(1|1)=0.85\\\\\n",
    "       q1: P(0|0)=0.98, P(1|0)=0.02, P(0|1)=0.1, P(1|1)=0.9\\\\\n",
    "       q2: P(0|0)=0.93, P(1|0)=0.07, P(0|1)=0.2, P(1|1)=0.8\\\\ \n",
    "       q3: P(0|0)=0.96, P(1|0)=0.04, P(0|1)=0.08, P(1|1)=0.92\\\\    \n",
    "       q4: P(0|0)=0.9, P(1|0)=0.1, P(0|1)=0.25, P(1|1)=0.75\\\\\n",
    "       q5: P(0|0)=0.97, P(1|0)=0.03, P(0|1)=0.1, P(1|1)=0.9\\\\\n",
    "       q6: P(0|0)=0.89, P(1|0)=0.11, P(0|1)=0.25, P(1|1)=0.75$\n",
    "    </p>\n",
    "     <p>\n",
    "        <li> Coupling map </li>\n",
    "         $[[0, 1], [1, 0], [1, 2], [1, 3], [2, 1], [3, 1], [3, 5], [4, 5], [5, 3], [5, 4], [5, 6], [6, 5]]$ \n",
